 164 entries reflecting the full breadth of human passion. The volume offers a fascinating introduction to Leopardi’s arguments and insights, as well as a glimpse of the concerns of thinkers to come, among them Nietzsche, Dostoyevsky, Wittgenstein, Gadda, and Beckett.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aItalian languagey19th century. 0aItalian literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Essays.2bisacsh1 aParks, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030018633840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018660440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300186604423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300186604/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY